@endnode

@node history "History of LCD Clock"
v1.2 (15. October 1999) - Due to a bug in the source code RGB mode wasn't
working properly if the screen had 256 colours. It took me all this time to get
to even test it! Sheesh! Anyway, it's fixed now.
v1.1 (27. April 1999) - LCD Clock can now appear on any public screen. It also
reads its icon's tool types when started from Workbench. Furthermore, it no
longer uses IntuiTicks, so it doesn't freeze up when its window isn't active.
v1.0 (11. April 1999) - First public release
@endnode
